.TH git-daft-skill-uninstall 1  "git-daft-skill-uninstall 1.20.0" 
.SH NAME
git\-daft\-skill\-uninstall \- Remove the installed agent skill
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgit\-daft\-skill\-uninstall\fR [\fB\-\-project\fR] [\fB\-\-dir\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-quiet\fR] [\fB\-v\fR|\fB\-\-verbose\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Removes an agent skill previously written by `git daft skill install` (the
daft\-worktree\-workflow skill).
.PP
By default it removes the user\-global copy
(~/.claude/skills/daft\-worktree\-workflow/). Use \-\-project to remove the
current worktree\*(Aqs .claude/skills/ copy, or \-\-dir to target another
agent\*(Aqs skills root.
.PP
Removal is safe by construction: only a SKILL.md whose frontmatter marks
it as the daft skill is deleted, and the daft\-worktree\-workflow directory
is removed only when nothing else is left inside it, so files you keep
beside the skill are preserved. A missing skill is a no\-op, not an error.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-project\fR
Remove from the current worktree\*(Aqs .claude/skills/ instead of ~/.claude/skills
.TP
\fB\-\-dir\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Remove from this skills root (for agents other than Claude Code)
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress the result line
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show detailed progress
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH VERSION
v1.20.0
